spanishExample: ¿Crees que hay tres millones siete mil animales en el mar?
englishTranslation: Do you think there are three million seven thousand animals in the sea?

spanishExample: Siendo honesto, nunca he visto nieve en el río.
englishTranslation: Being honest, I’ve never seen snow in the river.

spanishExample: No toque ninguno de los sesenta y dos millones.
englishTranslation: (Formal) Don’t touch any of the sixty-two million.

spanishExample: Noventa y ocho millones doscientas mil personas estaban ahí, viendo el juego.
englishTranslation: Ninety-eight million two hundred thousand people were there, watching the game.

spanishExample: Te toca, pero siendo honesto, no deberías jugar.
englishTranslation: It’s your turn, but being honest, you shouldn’t play.

spanishExample: El lago tiene un millón de animales.
englishTranslation: The lake has a million animals.

spanishExample: Hay dos millones ciento diez mil personas en esa ciudad.
englishTranslation: There are two million one hundred ten thousand people in that city.

spanishExample: ¡Si tocas frente a cuarenta y ocho millones de personas, será genial!
englishTranslation: If you play in front of forty-eight million people, it’ll be great!

spanishExample: Les ha encantado la isla con siete millones cuatrocientas mil personas.
englishTranslation: They have loved the island with seven million four hundred thousand people.

spanishExample: Miles de personas estaban aquí, escuchando el piano.
englishTranslation: Thousands of people were here, listening to the piano.

spanishExample: Nos encantó la playa y nos gustaría regresar al sol.
englishTranslation: We loved the beach and we would love to go back to the sun.

spanishExample: Siendo honestos, quinientos cuarenta y cuatro millones son demasiados.
englishTranslation: Being honest(plural), five hundred and forty-four million are too many.

spanishExample: No ha tocado frente a quinientos cincuenta millones de personas.
englishTranslation: She hasn’t played in front of five hundred and fifty million people.

spanishExample: Quiere que yo toque el piano porque suena bien.
englishTranslation: She wants me to play the piano because it sounds good.

spanishExample: Tocó esa canción con la guitarra.
englishTranslation: She played that song with the guitar.

spanishExample: ¡No toques eso! Lo has estado tocando por horas.
englishTranslation: Don’t play that! You’ve been playing it for hours.

spanishExample: Me encanta esa planta, es una de los ochocientos noventa y siete millones de tipos.
englishTranslation: I love that plant, it’s one of the eight hundred and ninety-seven million types.

spanishExample: No quiero que toque los siete millones seiscientos mil dólares.
englishTranslation: I don’t want him to touch the seven million six hundred thousand dollars.

spanishExample: ¡Toquen esa canción, les encantará!
englishTranslation: (Plural) Play that song, they will love it!

spanishExample: Quiero que toques la guitarra frente a treinta y nueve millones de personas.
englishTranslation: I want you to play the guitar in front of thirty-nine million people.

spanishExample: No queremos que todos ellos toquen, uno basta.
englishTranslation: We don’t want all of them to play; one does the trick.

spanishExample: Esto tiene que sonar bien para todos esos millones de personas.
englishTranslation: This has to sound good for all those millions of people.

spanishExample: Ella es honesta y dice que no le duele nada.
englishTranslation: She is honest and she says nothing hurts.

spanishExample: Hay más de dos mil seiscientos millones.
englishTranslation: There are over two billion six hundred million.

spanishExample: Toca la guitarra, pero no quiere tocar hoy.
englishTranslation: He plays the guitar, but he doesn’t want to play today.

spanishExample: No toco música.
englishTranslation: I don’t play music.

spanishExample: Hay seis millones ciento cincuenta mil árboles en ese bosque.
englishTranslation: There are six million one hundred and fifty thousand trees in that forest.

spanishExample: Había ciento treinta millones de personas en la naturaleza, mirando la luna.
englishTranslation: There were one hundred and thirty million people in nature, looking at the moon.
